{  Associate file types with programs #assoc_file_types

  Starting a perlscript (for example `foo.pl`) without suffix and without prefixing it with perl: `c:\> foo`.

  gh|Configure-Windows|/assoc_ftype_perl.bat||


}
{ cmd.exe #cmd_exe


  gh|Configure-Windows|/console.reg||

  See also the → Windows/registry[registry] key → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/console[`HKCU\Console`] for configuring → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe.

}
{ Turning off most sounds

  See → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/AppEvents/Schemes/Apps[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\AppEvents\Schemes\Apps`]

}
{ Explorer

  gh|Configure-Windows|/explorer.bat||

}
{ Environment variables

  → Windows/development/environment-variables[Environment variables] can be set in the following keys:
    • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Control/Session-Manager/Environment[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Environment`]
    • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Environment[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Environment`]

}
